result.execSummary:
The defendant Talia L Lowe was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Talia L Lowe is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Talia L Lowe was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: $265.60 fine/costs to be paid to the Clerk of Court Office with payment plan of $25.00 per month commencing on April 1, 2016 and the first of each month thereafter until paid in full. Failure to pay will be warrant.

Must provide DNA sample and pay the $200.00 DNA surcharge to Clerk of Court Office which will be added to established payment plan. Failure to pay will be warrant.   Defendant may request expungement of the DNA sample under Wis. Stat. 165.77(4) by petitioning the Wisconsin Department of Justice. Expungement of DNA is NOT a court process. 
For information see: http://www.doj.state.wi.us/dles/crime-labs/clb-forms.
Eligible for expungment upon successful completion of Probation.  Must petition court.
